		<h1 id="header">About</h1>
		<img class="profile-pic" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/69/Linus_Torvalds.jpeg/330px-Linus_Torvalds.jpeg" width="200px" align="right" alt="Linus folding his arms">
		<p>Here you will find a timeline of his life:</p>
		<ul>
			<li id="b">Born in Helsinki, Finland in 1969.</li>
			<li id="b">Attended and taught computer science at Helsinki University	between	1988 and 1996.</li>
			<li id="b">Began developing Linux during this time after being dissatisfied with Microsoftâ€™s OS.</li>
			<li id="b">In 1997, Torvalds moved to California and began working at Transmeta Corporation.</li>
			<li id="b">In 2003, and began working for Open Source Development Labs, a conglomerate of companies such as IBM.</li>
			<li id="b">His role at OSDL was to continue the growth of Linux for it to be widely used in the corporate world.</li>
			<li id="b">In 2007, OSDL and Free Standards Group merged to become the Linux Foundation.</li>
			<li id="b">Currently Torvalds is residing in Oregon with his family as he o versees the continuous development of Linux.</li>
		</ul>
